The Voli is ultimate optic ready tactical carbine, with everything you need to add the tactical red dot sight or optic of your choice to have a complete rifle system. This rifle was built and configured with the patrol officer, tactical enthusiast, or self-defense user in mind. The Magpul MOE furniture provides comfortable, durable, and ergonomic benefits and the ease of adding accessories such as slings, lights, and storage for batteries and parts. The Magpul MOE line of products has numerous accessories making configuring your rifle for your needs simple. This rifle also features an ambidextrous safety selector lever from Battle Arms Development.

The mid-length direct impingement gas system is an improvement of then tried and trued operating system that has been in use by our armed forces for decades. The mid-length gas system provides a longer hand guard, providing more real estate for mounting accessories, allows for an extended more comfortable grip, and an increased length in sight radius. The mid-legth gas system also reduces the pressure to the gas operating system reducing stress on parts and components and providing a smoother and reduced recoil impulse. The gas tube has been Melonite treated for extra corrosion resistance and reliability.

The bolt carrier group is an M16 weight carrier made from 8620 steel and is finished inside and out with a new, cutting edge proprietary coating process by Adams Arms. This revolutionary new coating process offers multiple advantages over and above traditional current coating processes on the market today. These advantages include a harder surface level then hard chrome, superior lubricity properties, and excellent corrosion resistance, all superior to traditional Mil-Spec Parkerizing. The gas key is heat treated and finished with the same new coating process as the carrier, attached to the carrier with Grade 8 fasteners manufactured in the United States, and properly staked. The bolt is manufactured from proper Mil-Spec Carpenter No. 158 ® Steel, magnetic particle inspected (MPI), and has a carbine extractor spring, insert, and Crane O-ring.

The upper and lower receivers are machined from high quality mil-spec 7075-T6 aluminum forgings, with critical dimensions held within +-.001” and Type III Hardcoat finished. The mil spec receiver extension/buffer tube is precision machined from 7075-T6 aluminum as well. The magwell front features recessed chevrons for improved control. The front sight base is an F Marked base, the height of the base will match perfectly with rear sights mounted on the upper receiver, allowing you to sight in with out the addition of an extended length front sight post. The front sight base is also pinned for durability; the barrel is also finished under the front sight base."

Spanish Airforce Mauser All original and all matching numbers.Chambered in 8mm Mauser caliber marked ""Cal 7.92 [P] [R]"" on left side of receiver. 23 1/8"" barrel.There are no import marks defacing this rifle. This is NOT one of the more common Spanish made La Coruna M43 rifles.""S/42G"" marked rear sight, ""lxr"" marked magazine follower. Bolt, trigger-guard, floor-plate and receiver are all matching, other parts are un-numbered, as is correct for these rifles. Shiny and prominent Spanish Airforce eagle crest stamped center of receiver. Maintains 95% original bluing, walnut stock is in good condition except for small crack above rear stock plate. Nice prominent rifling, with some pitting which is typical for these rifles. Battled Communists in the streets of Germany during the Weimar Republic era, served in the early Nazi era German Army, and then went on to kill working class anarchists in the Spanish Civil War before being rebuilt for the Spanish Airforce in the late WW2 era. It has it's original correct cleaning rod, Spanish black leather sling with the distinctive Spanish curved brass buckle, correct Spanish bayonet along with bayonet scabbard and bayonet frog, that is a slightly lighter and thinner version of the German Mauser 98k bayonet, correct original muzzle cap cover made specifically for the Kar 98a front sight, and two black leather Spanish ammo pouches one marked ""EPI"". These are all scarce and desirable items that are worth it by themselves. This rifle is very difficult to find with all its' original accessories along with being in the condition that it is. This rifle is meant for collector's specifically Mauser enthusiasts, it has a lot of history behind it especially if you have read ""Homage to Catalonia"" by George Orwell. Made for Spanish military, high quality military craftsmanship unlike the common M43 Spanish Mausers which had heat treatment issues. $1500

Peruvian Model 1909 that was manufactured prior to WWI by Mauser in Oberndorf Germany.The first and original Mauser factory. Has ""Waffenfabrik Mauser-Oberndorf A/N"" left side receiver. Has the Lange Visier (""Roller Coaster"") long-range rear sight. It has a 29.13"" barrel with German ""H"" style bayonet lug. This rifle is beautifully made (pre-WWI build quality and attention to detail was absolutely superb) and is nicely marked with the Peruvian crest on the receiver partially removed, under which is marked ""MAUSER ORIGINAL"". This rifle is completely original.It is NOT import marked. The original blue finish rates about 80%. The stock is in very good shape with handling wear no cracks or chips...and never sanded or refinished. The mechanics are in good working order and the bore is sharp and bright. A nice example of a very hard to find South American contract Mauser rifle.Safety is marked ""56"", bolt shroud ""56"", bolt ""3359"" and receiver ""30988"". If you need more pictures of how the rifle looks just ask. $550.
